# Taste + Cursor Skills (Permanent)

This project has two skill libraries. **Before any matching task, read the relevant `SKILL.md` and follow it completely.** Do not improvise design or workflow when a skill exists.

## Library 1 — Taste Skills (design / frontend)

**Path:** `.agents/skills/`  
**Source:** `Leonxlnx/taste-skill` (see `skills-lock.json`)

| Skill | Use when |
|---|---|
| `design-taste-frontend` | Landing pages, portfolios, redesigns, anti-slop UI (default) |
| `design-taste-frontend-v1` | Backward-compatible v1 behavior only |
| `gpt-taste` | GSAP, AIDA, bento grids, scroll motion |
| `image-to-code` | Visual work: generate image(s) first, analyze, then code |
| `imagegen-frontend-web` | Web mockups — **one horizontal image per section** |
| `imagegen-frontend-mobile` | Mobile app screen mockups (images only) |
| `brandkit` | Brand identity boards, logo systems |
| `minimalist-ui` | Warm monochrome editorial minimal UI |
| `industrial-brutalist-ui` | Brutalist / Swiss print / terminal UI |
| `high-end-visual-design` | Awwwards-tier motion and components |
| `redesign-existing-projects` | Upgrade existing sites without breaking behavior |
| `stitch-design-taste` | Generate `DESIGN.md` for Google Stitch |
| `full-output-enforcement` | Full files, no `// ...` or placeholders |

**Taste defaults to enforce:** no Inter-by-default, no AI-purple gradients, no em-dash (`—`), hero ≤2–3 lines, `min-h-[100dvh]`, generous spacing, Phosphor/HugeIcons over Lucide, image-first when visual quality matters.

## Library 2 — Cursor Built-in Skills

**Path:** `~/.cursor/skills-cursor/` (read-only; do not write here)

| Skill | Use when |
|---|---|
| `automate` | User asks for **Cursor Automation** (not generic CI/scripts) |
| `babysit` | Keep a PR merge-ready (comments, conflicts, CI) |
| `canvas` | Standalone analysis — charts, tables, audits → `.canvas.tsx` |
| `create-hook` | `.cursor/hooks.json` and hook scripts |
| `create-rule` | `.cursor/rules/` project rules |
| `create-skill` | Author new `SKILL.md` files |
| `loop` | `/loop [interval] <prompt>` recurring tasks |
| `review-bugbot` | `/review-bugbot` — launch bugbot subagent |
| `review-security` | Security review subagent |
| `sdk` | `@cursor/sdk` / `cursor-sdk` programmatic agents |
| `split-to-prs` | Split work into small reviewable PRs |
| `statusline` | CLI status line in `cli-config.json` |
| `update-cursor-settings` | Cursor/VS Code `settings.json` |

## Routing (quick)

- **New premium website / UI** → `design-taste-frontend` (+ `image-to-code` or `imagegen-frontend-web` if visuals first)
- **Redesign existing site** → `redesign-existing-projects` + `design-taste-frontend`
- **Mobile app visuals** → `imagegen-frontend-mobile`
- **Brand deck** → `brandkit`
- **Complete code output** → `full-output-enforcement`
- **PR / review / automation / hooks / SDK** → matching Cursor skill from Library 2

Respond to the user in **Persian** unless they write in another language.
